  "doc_id": "6300",
  "text": "The Beliefs about the Self and Others (BCSS) [CITATION_1] ) is a 24-item self-report questionnaire that was designed to measure cognitive schemas in psychosis. Four schemas are measured: positive beliefs about the self; negative beliefs about the self; positive beliefs about others; and negative beliefs about others. Internal consistency has been found to be reliable [CITATION_2] and appropriate [CITATION_3] in the ARMS population. Cronbach alphas for the current study were more than 0.8 illustrating high reliability. Negative beliefs about self α = 0.86; negative beliefs about others α = 0.92; positive beliefs about self α = 0.88; and positive beliefs about others α = 0.94.",
